programme.title: Pickaxe Murders
programme.desc: Houston, Texas is rocked by a grisly crime scene - a man whose head is practically hammered off his body and a semi-nude woman riddled with pickaxe wounds. The final blow leaves the pickaxe impaled through her heart with such force that it is embedded into the floor. The police uncover an unlikely suspect - a petite woman who claims to get sexual satisfaction from killing.

programme.title: Fast Food Massacre
programme.desc: A Wendy's restaurant in Queens, New York is hit by a pair of robbers just before closing time. The robbery escalates as the pair slaughter five employees, leaving another two for dead. The crime unravels into a story of revenge and betrayal when one survivor reveals to police what he witnessed.

programme.title: Bound To Die
programme.desc: Nineteen-year-old Elizabeth "Lizzi" Marriott goes missing. Her co-worker, Kat McDonough, admits to offering the teen up for rough sex with her dominant boyfriend, Seth Mazzaglia - an act that resulted in Marriot's death.

programme.title: Texas Tower Sniper
programme.desc: In America's first mass slaying, a sniper randomly guns down students and pedestrians from atop the University of Texas clock tower. Police are out-gunned and are floundering. It's pandemonium until three strangers - two cops and a civilian who has taken the law into his own hands - join forces.

programme.title: The Killer Nurse
programme.desc: When patients start mysteriously dying at hospitals in New Jersey and Pennsylvania, the rumor is that a serial killer is at work. The investigation leads police to one of the night shift nurses - Charles Cullen, a meek man who finds God-like power by having life and death control over others.

programme.title: Snuff Film Killers
programme.desc: When a fisherman in Bates City, Missouri discovers the nude body of a woman, police are led to an ex-con and his girlfriend. Their investigation uncovers a videotape of the two sexually assaulting and murdering the victim, as well as another woman.

programme.title: Christmas Eve Massacre
programme.desc: A man wearing a Santa suit makes a surprise visit to a family Christmas Eve party. The man is carrying a gift-wrapped flamethrower in one hand and a handgun in the other. The man opens fire, then sets the house ablaze, killing nine.

programme.title: The Fiendish Friend
programme.desc: When Julie Kibuishi is murdered and her boyfriend Samuel Herr turns up missing, police assume is on the run. Herr's credit card leads them to his friend, Daniel Wozniak, who soon admits to stealing from Herr to finance his own wedding and then murdering the pair to cover up the crime.

programme.title: Hometown Tragedy
programme.desc: It's the day after Thanksgiving 1992 in Drake, Iowa, and few want to cook. Locals head to the popular Drake Diner instead. In front of a packed restaurant, an armed man shoots and kills two diner employees. Is the town as peaceful as some say?

programme.title: Hometown Tragedy
programme.desc: Six people are slain in a home in a quiet Iowa town. One person survives a gunshot to the head and claims to have no memory of the incident. The tragedy and eventual trial shred the social fabric of the neighborhood.

programme.title: Ed & Day in The 'Burgh
programme.desc: Ed and Day venture to Verona and explore “the spot that’s more than a dot.” The guys play pickleball, dine on BBQ, get creative with splatter paint, and finish the day with a brew.

programme.title: Wait, What Happened?
programme.desc: Frank Nicotero asks contestants about real news stories with unreal outcomes to see if they can win cash. In "Animals Gone Wild," locals learn about a lobster diver in a shocking predicament, creatures cruising in cars and a bull in an odd place.

programme.title: Lost Innocence: The Tragedy of Harmony Montgomery
programme.desc: A police investigation into a missing seven-year-old girl in Manchester, New Hampshire reveals harrowing details that shock the state. But even more disturbing is the discovery that the tragic outcome could have been avoided.

programme.title: Eat Play Stay
programme.desc: ‘Fight for your right’ to start the day right with a ‘90s-themed breakfast. Climb aboard a bicycle built for twelve, and cruise between boozy destinations that feature everything from classy cocktails to intoxicating IV bags.

programme.title: Blind Kitchen
programme.desc: Chef Scott from Creole BBQ can’t stop singing, and Chef Octavio from the Good Trouble Network won’t slow down. It’s a fast and furious blindfold battle…packed with a whole lot of giggles.

programme.title: Hour Long Docs List
programme.desc: A playlist of hour long VL Originals

programme.title: Hometown Tragedy
programme.desc: The disappearance of 16-year-old JaRay Wilson spawns rumors of human trafficking in her small town in 2012. Investigators find her body and the truth, after an unlikely informant provides new details.

programme.title: Chaos & Kindness
programme.desc: Meet Pat and Patty, an engaged couple who fell on hard times while planning their dream wedding. The team comes together to throw these two a special day they'll never forget!

programme.title: What's On The Menu?
programme.desc: Baking and confections are a science. These Greenville sweet spots, Brick Street Cafe, Buttermilk Sky Pie, Better Than Sex, and Old Europe Cafe show us how they get the chemistry in their flavors exactly right!

programme.title: Plate It!
programme.desc: You can’t have Sacramento without the Kings, and you can’t have the Kings without some seriously delicious grub. Chef Sara Arbabian is up against Chef Greg Desmangles to serve up an upscale take on their favorite courtside dishes.

programme.title: Hometown Tragedy
programme.desc: Single father Kendal Fenwick is the 295th homicide in Baltimore in 2015. Family and investigators wonder whether his efforts to curb drugs and violence in his neighborhood made him a target. Or is it something else entirely?

programme.title: Absolutely Albuquerque
programme.desc: MMA champion Michelle Waterson-Gomez takes Amanda on a high-energy day in Albuquerque. From throwing punches inside the octagon to dancing up high on aerial silks, this dynamic duo never seems to break a sweat.

programme.title: Local Love
programme.desc: After being divorced for 15 years Angelina is looking for love in all the right places in Sacramento with three local bachelors. But she’s going to have her work cut out for her as she goes bowling, talks classic cars and completes an escape room.

programme.title: Boston Rob Does Beantown
programme.desc: Rob takes on ocean conservation and masters sculling, plus proves he’s got the skills to perform on Boston’s bluest stage with some world-famous performers.

programme.title: Eat Play Stay
